verbose_text: The significant reduction in TNF-alpha and IL-6 levels was observed in cells treated with free SA in comparison to those with LPS (both p < 0.01, Figure XREF_FIG A and XREF_FIG B), despite the reduction with SA-PEG was no statistical significance in comparison to LPS, which is probably due to the delayed release of SA dissociating from SA-PEG.
